  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning-augmented CFD hemolysis prediction pipeline applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. A feedforward neural network surrogate (3 hidden layers, 128 units each, ReLU activations) is trained on CFD-derived shear-stress histories to predict the relative hemolysis index (RHI) across 5 flow-speed combinations. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Reproducibility of the neural network was studied informally during development; no quantitative seed-to-seed variance characterization is reported in this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-ml-rhi-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/ml-surrogate-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/ffnn-hemolysis-surrogate-v1",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cfd-shear-history-training-set",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-benchmark-validation-set"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/ml-surrogate-holdout-performance",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Neural network surrogate holdout validation — single training run",
      "description": "The FFNN surrogate was trained on 1,200 CFD-derived operating-point records (80/20 train-holdout split, fixed partition). A single training run with a fixed random seed (seed=42) was used for the reported results. Holdout RMSE for RHI prediction: 0.031 (dimensionless); R² = 0.974. Mean absolute percentage error across the 5 target flow-speed combinations: 2.8%. The surrogate correctly ranked all five operating points by hemolysis severity, consistent with full CFD results. Reproducibility was studied informally during model development; the team noted qualitative consistency across a small number of exploratory runs but did not systematically quantify variance attributable to weight initialization or stochastic gradient descent across multiple seeds."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cfd-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD-to-experimental hemolysis index comparison (FDA benchmark)",
      "description": "The underlying CFD model (Fluent 2023R1, k-omega SST turbulence, power-law hemolysis model) was validated against FDA-published experimental hemolysis data for the generic centrifugal pump at 2500 and 3500 RPM, 3 and 6 L/min. Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions fell within ±15% of experimental measurements across all four validation conditions, meeting the MRL 2 acceptance criterion of ±20%. This validation pertains to the physics-based CFD layer; the ML surrogate layer is assessed separately in the holdout validation above."
    }
  ],
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4041740",
