      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating GCI < 5% for NIH quantity of interest at the selected mesh density.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.1M, fine 7.8M cells) performed at 3500 RPM / 5 L/min. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 3.2% for NIH between medium and fine meshes. Medium mesh selected for production runs, with GCI below the 5% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) reproduced in simulation within ±5% of nominal test values.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions (fluid: glycerol-water mixture, viscosity 0.00345 Pa·s at 37°C; flow rates 3 and 6 L/min; speeds 2500 and 3500 RPM) are replicated in CFD boundary conditions. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream pipe fully-developed flow assumption, consistent with experimental setup. Deviation from nominal conditions is less than 2% for all parameters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
