      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest (RHI, NIH) are directly linked to the regulatory hemolysis acceptance criterion and clinical risk metric.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RHI < 1) is the primary regulatory acceptance criterion per ASTM F1841 and ISO 10993-4 hemolysis guidance. NIH is the standard experimental comparator. The ML surrogate is trained and evaluated exclusively on these quantities. QoI relevance is confirmed by the clinical and regulatory mapping documented in the COU description."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
