      "rationale": "CFD inputs (geometry, boundary conditions, fluid properties) are fully documented with measurement sources and tolerances. ML surrogate inputs (shear stress history features: mean, peak, exposure time per operating point) are derived deterministically from CFD post-processing. One-at-a-time sensitivity study across ±10% variation in impeller tip clearance and flow rate confirms RHI monotonic response, supporting surrogate interpolation validity."
    },
