    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-ml-hemolysis-cou1-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are within scope of MRL 2 exemptions. The neural network surrogate demonstrates strong holdout performance (R²=0.974, MAPE 2.8%) on a single training run, and the underlying CFD layer meets experimental validation criteria. The assessment team notes that reproducibility across training seeds was studied informally and found to be qualitatively consistent; this was judged sufficient for the current submission. The composite evidence package supports the conclusion that the ML-augmented CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions under the defined COU, and the decision to accept the model for regulatory submission is warranted.",
